    Leah Ranta3 months ago on Google
    3/5
    Best part of this hotel is the location! Has everything you would need, but if sensitive to noise/light/temperature will struggle with sleeping. 
    Best part of this hotel is the location! Has everything you would need, but if sensitive to noise/light/temperature will struggle with sleeping.
    Location: Close to lots of restaurants. Across the street is a rooftop restaurant where you can see views of the, walkable to FRS ferry (to Spain)
    Amenities: Lots of lounge space, bar with bottled water (20 Dirams) or alcohol, restaurant, rooftop pool, bathrooms, piano, pool table
    Taxi: Tons close by, quick drive to train station (6 min), look for little light blue ones and pay 20 dirahms
    Breakfast: Not free, be sure to pay before leaving
    Noise: Loud all night
    Air conditioning: Okay, works but still warm due to Morocco summer
    Pool: Up on rooftop, perfect temperature, pretty shallow, bring your own towel from room as none up top
    Family Room: Great! 3 beds, 2 rooms, 1 bath, cleanliness is okay - bathroom quite aged, no light blocking shades
    Customer Service: Friendly front desk, clean room every night but dont leave clean towels

    Kenneth Tangerois3 Maroc2 years ago on Google
    4/5
    Hotel Tanjah Flandria is an established moderately-priced hotel on Avenue Mohammed V in downtown Tangier, Morocco. It is clean and and convenient to restaurants, shops and cafs, the Medina and Place de France. 
    Hotel Tanjah Flandria is an established moderately-priced hotel on Avenue Mohammed V in downtown Tangier, Morocco. It is clean and and convenient to restaurants, shops and cafs, the Medina and Place de France.
    There is a rooftop terrace with a small swimming pool that offers a panoramic view of the city and ocean. On the first floor is a terrace caf overlooking the Boulevard Pasteur which is pleasant, particularly on summer evenings.
    The rooms are on the small size but they are comfortable and air-conditioned the bathrooms are good and have plenty of hot water. There is also a restaurant which serves a variety of food at reasonable prices. Credit cards are accepted.

    About this hotel

    This relaxed hotel near shops and eateries is a 10-minute walk from the Grand Socco market square, 1 km from Municipale Beach and 14 km from Tangier Ibn Battouta Airport.

    Warmly furnished rooms provide flat-screen TVs with satellite channels.

    Amenities include a restaurant, an outdoor pool and a spa, in addition to a bar, a nightclub and a hair/beauty salon. Parking and breakfast are available.
